author: Fiona Flynn
title: TV | Later Live... with Jools Holland
text: Jools has yet again a gathering of exceptional musical talent on his show tonight, as the legends Duran Duran perform a couple of tracks from their 14th studio album Paper Gods. As well as that, the awesome Public Image Ltd play tracks from their recent 10th studio album, What the World Needs Now. While also on the show will be alt-R'n'B exponent Miguel, Canadian singer-songwriter Frazey Ford and north London-based newcomers Wolf Alice - who have recently been nominated for the Mercury Music Prize.
